social_posts.post_text: New Episode of Synthesized Radio 📻- This month’s episode we showcase several tracks that are featured on the Drumcode’s A-Sides Compilation Vol. 11. The mighty A-Sides Compilation as well features my record ’Traction’ which is Out Now on all platforms.

What an amazing Drumcode Party at Warehouse Project in Manchester 🤩 within 20 mins of opening the doors the archive room was buzzing, It was so much fun to play my first show in the UK. Can’t wait to come back ! 🖤🖤🖤

Some of the most memorable moments this year for me have been when I hear my tracks, remixes, edits, etc being played and I’m there to witness it firsthand. As a Producer/ Artist there is no better feeling when your music is being played by others, and most importantly from the boss himself. Here is Adam Beyer dropping Final Chapter in Manchester 🔔 🔔 @whp_mcr x @drumcoderecords

Few Weeks back @elsewherespace … always fun playing in NY! Looking forward to the next one 🖤

Which one is your favorite ? 1,2,3, or 4? 🙃

2022 has been an incredible year filled with so many amazing moments. I’m extremely grateful that I was able to fully tour this past year and visit so many new countries & breathtaking places. 

Big love to all the promoters and talent buyers out there that booked me to play. 

Some of the highlights for me was being able to release on my dream label , Drumcode, playing at Resistance in Guatemala, doing 3 incredible shows with Eric Prydz in April, and playing in Medellín.

I really appreciate all the fans that came out to support and I’m really looking forward to what 2023 has in store.  Special shout out to all my NY fans, you guys really came out for me throughout the year 🖤

Here are a few videos recapping some super special moments throughout the past year. Which video is your favorite ??

Bring on 2023 ☄️☄️☄️

BIG LOVE for all the Support this year from the fans and DJ’s that played my music ❤️

As a thank you here is my remix of (Brainbug - Nightmare) as a Free Download! 

I’ve been playing this remix for over an year now, and it’s been a huge part of my live sets. It’s prolly one of my favorite records to play when played at the right time in the night.  I’m happy now to share it with everyone 😌

Hope everyone has a Happy New Year and let’s bring on 2023! 

Charles 🖤

[Out Now] ! ! 🔔 🔔 It’s Coming …. My Remix of ‘Final Chapter’ the iconic NYC anthem of the late 90’s and early 2000’s by Mike Macaluso is coming out on Drumcode on April 7th. Living in New York for 32 years, it’s an amazing feeling to pay homage to the city by remixing this record. It’s a full circle moment for me as an artist. Big thanks to Adam Beyer for supporting this remix throughout his sets, and I couldn’t be more thrilled for it to come out on @drumcoderecords. And of course much love to Mike for giving his blessing for me to remix his iconic record! 🔔 🔔

#drumcoode4life

🔔🔔🔔 My remix for Mike Macaluso’s ‘Final Chapter’ is OUT NOW on @drumcoderecords . Super excited for this one to be released, and big thanks to @djmikemacaluso for giving his blessing and allowing this to happen. 

I made this remix last summer when my best friend was sharing some classic records with me, and I instantly remembered this one … it was literally the soundtrack to NYC nightlife in the early 2000’s … being played at iconic venues such Sound Factory, Pacha, Avalon, & Tunnel. Instantly, I knew right away I had to make a remix of it. Soon after, @realadambeyer debuted it at Lovelands over the summer. The most unforgettable moment had to be when Adam played it at Brooklyn Mirage in New York and the crowd went absolutely crazy! Being there to witness it all myself was such a full circle moment for me. 🖤🖤
🔔 🔔 🔔 - Final Chapter (Charles D Remix) Out Now 💫🖤

I had an absolute blast opening things up for @realadambeyer at Nebula this past Friday.

It was my birthday a few weeks ago and it marked 10 years exactly of when I first started to produce music. That’s almost one third of my life! Even though at times there were many doubts, I had to trust the process all the way through while still staying authentic to myself and not taking any shortcuts along the way. I’ve never been happier and more stressed in my life, and wouldn’t have it any other way. Just wanted to give a big thank you to my team, my family & friends, my beautiful girlfriend, and of course all the fans for all your support. 🖤🖤

📸 @hitmanjason

‘Believer’ with @madeaux is Out Now!.. this one is something a little different from myself personally, less hard hitting and a bit more melodic.… I don’t usually release full vocal tracks often, but felt it was the right time to do so. Madeaux was incredible to work with, and we both felt it was time that ‘Believer’ got released. Right in time for summer. Hope y’all like it ! 🖤🖤

Excited to be on Drumcode Radio this week! Big thanks for @drumcoderecords and @realadambeyer for having me back once again! The episode is full of unreleased ID’s from myself and music from Space 92, Tini Gessler, Rebuke, & James Blvck. The mix also features my latest release on Drumcode which is my remix of Mike Macaluso’s classic anthem ‘Final Chapter.’ We both got in the studio a few weeks back and talked about the NYC nightlife scene in the late 90’s and early 2000’s, listened to other classics during that epic time in NYC nightlife, and also got a chance to just have great conversation about life, family, happiness, and of course music.
